Voting and announcement of results for the about 78 positions up for grabs at the APC national convention ended at about 8.40am on Sunday. Chairman of the Convention Election Committee and Jigawa State Governor Muhammad Badaru Abubakar said the new leadership will be sworn in at about 11am when President Muhammadu Buhari is expected to return to the venue.   2023: If Tinubu, Rochas ticket emanates, I’ll clinch it –…     Investments in free trade zone worth $20bn, says Minister     How to lift millions out of poverty, by don   Meanwhile, a majority of delegates have departed the Eagle Square leaving behind a huge waste for the cleaners to deal with. A trip in and around the Eagle Square revealed heaps of used water cans, papers bags and packs of takeaways.